{"id": "GB-003", "role": "eng", "type": "answerable", "query": "What is the vibration inspection interval?", "answer": "- The context does not provide a specific vibration inspection interval. However, it mentions that careful inspections of the cooling system, which may include checking for vibrations, should be made once each watch or at intervals deemed necessary by the engineering officer (Source 1).\n\n- For vibration analysis in general, engineers inspect systems to understand vibrational patterns and magnitudes, which can affect the strength and stiffness of structures (Source 2). However, no specific interval is mentioned for these inspections.\n\n- The documents related to vibration tests on containers and tanks do not specify inspection intervals but describe inspections conducted immediately after tests and after a 24-hour period (Sources 3, 4, 7).\n\n- The ISO 13373 document discusses vibration condition monitoring and analysis but does not specify inspection intervals (Sources 5, 6).\n\nExact: Not present in provided documents.", "sources": [{"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\autocad_docs\\DieselEngineMaintenance.pdf", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.7133129125309157, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\autocad_docs\\oschsner_augustin.pdf", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.7071830337805687, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\logistics_analyst_docs\\DTIC_ADA275506.pdf", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.6266934204101563, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\logistics_analyst_docs\\DTIC_ADA256934.pdf", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.6147390526816958, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\e