{"id": "GB-007", "role": "cyber", "type": "answerable", "query": "What transport protocol is approved?", "answer": "- The Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) is approved as a transport protocol. It operates at the same level as UDP and TCP, providing reliable transport services similar to TCP (Source 1).\n\n- Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) uses TCP as its transport protocol. TCP is chosen because it meets BGP's requirements for a reliable transport protocol and is widely available in commercial routers and hosts (Source 2).\n\n- For the transport of certain protocols over IP, both TCP and UDP/ALF are implemented by Media Gateway Controllers (MGCs), while Media Gateways (MGs) can implement either TCP, UDP/ALF, or both (Sources 3 and 4).\n\nExact: Not present in provided documents.", "sources": [{"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\system_administrator_docs\\rfc_standards\\rfc3286.txt", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.9302314521420387, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\system_administrator_docs\\rfc_standards\\rfc1771.txt", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.8697407765964884, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\system_administrator_docs\\rfc_standards\\rfc2885.txt", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.7059184790735156, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\system_administrator_docs\\rfc_standards\\rfc3015.txt", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.7010986344666343, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Educational\\data\\source\\system_administrator_docs\\rfc_standards\\rfc1191.txt", "chunks": 1, "avg_relevance": 0.6960638670996557, "access_tags": ["shared"], "access_tag_source": "default_document_tags"}, {"path": "C:\\HybridRAG3_Edu